take a different form than in the pileup process, as shown in Fig. 4a. Here, it can be observed that the plastic\par
slip on two sides of the grain boundary converges not to a single point, but to two points apart, and the distance\par
between them increases, which means that the misorientation of the grain boundary increases. To see the effect\par
of the additionally accumulated non-redundant dislocations, we omit the jump from the plastic slip distribution\par
